            <ab>(from l. 8): ". . . but the phantom also signed (to me) to thrust, and seemed to urge me on. So, cheerfully and gladly, as if killing an enemy, I slew myself. When I had fallen and died, I recognized the phantom. It was Seueris and . . ."</ab>
